---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { CookieOptOut } from '../components/CookieOptOut';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy - Michigan Spots"
  description="Cookie Policy for Michigan Spots platform"
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-6">Cookie Policy</h1>

      <p class="text-sm text-ink-faded mb-8">
        <strong>Effective Date:</strong> October 15, 2025<br />
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> October 15, 2025
      </p>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help websites remember your preferences, improve functionality, and provide analytics about site usage. Michigan Spots uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.1 Essential Cookies (Always Active)</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          These cookies are necessary for the Platform to function and cannot be disabled:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Session Management:</strong> Maintains your login state via Reddit authentication</li>
          <li><strong>Security:</strong> Protects against CSRF attacks and ensures secure connections</li>
          <li><strong>Form Functionality:</strong> Remembers form inputs during multi-step processes</li>
          <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> Records your cookie preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.2 Functional Cookies (Optional)</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          These cookies enhance functionality and personalization:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>User Preferences:</strong> Remembers your display settings and language preferences</li>
          <li><strong>City Selection:</strong> Stores your Michigan city for personalized challenges</li>
          <li><strong>UI State:</strong> Remembers collapsed/expanded sections and view preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.3 Analytics Cookies (Optional)</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          These cookies help us understand how users interact with the Platform:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Tracks page views, popular features, and navigation patterns</li>
          <li><strong>Performance Monitoring:</strong> Identifies technical issues and load times</li>
          <li><strong>A/B Testing:</strong> Tests different features to improve user experience</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm italic">
          Analytics data is anonymized and aggregated. We use Cloudflare Analytics, which respects user privacy.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.4 Marketing Cookies (Optional)</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          These cookies support promotional activities:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Campaign Tracking:</strong> Measures effectiveness of marketing campaigns</li>
          <li><strong>Referral Source:</strong> Identifies how you found Michigan Spots</li>
          <li><strong>Social Media Integration:</strong> Enables sharing features on social platforms</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Michigan Spots integrates with third-party services that may set their own cookies:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-parchment-light border-2 border-ink-primary p-4 rounded mb-4">
          <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-2">Reddit</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Reddit sets cookies for authentication and platform integration. See <a href="https://www.reddit.com/policies/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">Reddit's Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-parchment-light border-2 border-ink-primary p-4 rounded mb-4">
          <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-2">Stripe</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Stripe uses cookies for payment processing and fraud prevention. See <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">Stripe's Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-parchment-light border-2 border-ink-primary p-4 rounded mb-4">
          <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-2">Cloudflare</h4>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Cloudflare sets cookies for security, performance, and analytics. See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">4. How to Manage Cookies</h2>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.1 Cookie Consent Banner</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
          When you first visit Michigan Spots, you'll see a cookie consent banner. You can accept all cookies, reject optional cookies, or customize your preferences. Your choice is saved and you can change it anytime by clicking "Cookie Settings" in the footer.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose mb-8">
          <CookieOptOut client:load />
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.2 Browser Settings</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          You can also manage cookies through your browser settings:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
          <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
          <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
          <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm italic">
          Note: Blocking essential cookies may prevent the Platform from functioning correctly.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.3 Mobile Devices</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          On mobile devices, you can manage cookies through your browser app's settings or device privacy settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">5. Cookie Duration</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Cookies may be session-based (deleted when you close your browser) or persistent (stored for a set period):
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> Authentication, security tokens (deleted after session ends)</li>
          <li><strong>Short-term Persistent:</strong> Form data, UI preferences (7-30 days)</li>
          <li><strong>Long-term Persistent:</strong> Cookie consent preferences, login state (up to 1 year)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">6. Do Not Track (DNT)</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Some browsers have a "Do Not Track" (DNT) feature that signals websites you don't want to be tracked. Michigan Spots respects DNT signals by limiting analytics and marketing cookie usage when DNT is enabled.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">7. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We may update this Cookie Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Updates will be posted on this page with a new "Last Updated" date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          For questions about our use of cookies, contact:<br />
          <strong>Cozyartz Media Group</strong><br />
          Battle Creek, Michigan<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@michiganspots.com" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">privacy@michiganspots.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="border-t-2 border-ink-primary pt-8 mt-12">
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-faded text-center">
          © 2025 Cozyartz Media Group. All rights reserved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  .prose h1, .prose h2, .prose h3, .prose h4 {
    color: inherit;
  }
  .prose ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .prose li {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
</style>
